HEADWORD: Sea cucumber
<hw>Sea" cu"cum*ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any large
holothurian, especially one of those belonging to the genus
<gen>Pentacta</gen>, or <gen>Cucumaria</gen>, as the common American and
European species. (<spn>Pentacta frondosa</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea dace</ent>⟦br⟧
